%F A068985 Equals 2*(1/3! + 2/5! + 3/7! + ...). [Jolley]
%F A068985 Equals 1 - Sum_{i >= 1} (-1)^(i - 1)/i!. [Michon]
%F A068985 Equals lim_{x->infinity} (1 - 1/x)^x. - _Arkadiusz Wesolowski_, Feb 17 2012
%F A068985 Equals j_1(i)/i = cos(i) + i*sin(i), where j_1(z) is the spherical Bessel function of the first kind and i = sqrt(-1). - _Stanislav Sykora_, Jan 11 2017
%F A068985 Equals Sum_{i>=0} ((-1)^i)/i!. - _Maciej Kaniewski_, Sep 10 2017
%F A068985 Equals Sum_{i>=0} ((-1)^i)(i^2+1)/i!. - _Maciej Kaniewski_, Sep 12 2017
%F A068985 From _Peter Bala_, Oct 23 2019: (Start)
%F A068985 The series representation 1/e = Sum_{k >= 0} (-1)^k/k! is the case n = 0 of the following series acceleration formulas:
%F A068985 1/e = n!*Sum_{k >= 0} (-1)^k/(k!*R(n,k)*R(n,k+1)), n = 0,1,2,..., where R(n,x) = Sum_{k = 0..n} (-1)^k*binomial(n,k)*k!*binomial(-x,k) are the row polynomials of A094816. (End)
%F A068985 1/e = 1 - Sum_{n >= 0} n!/(A(n)*A(n+1)), where A(n) = A000522(n). - _Peter Bala_, Nov 13 2019
%F A068985 Equals Integral_{x=0..1} x * sinh(x) dx. - _Amiram Eldar_, Aug 14 2020
%F A068985 Equals lim_{x->oo} (x!)^(1/x)/x. - _L. Joris Perrenet_, Dec 08 2020
%F A068985 Equals lim_{n->oo} (n+1)!^(1/(n+1)) - n!^(1/n) (Lalescu, 1900-1901). - _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 29 2022
%F A068985 Equals Sum_{n=-1..-oo} lim_{z->n} (z-n)*z!. - _Jwalin Bhatt_, Sep 23 2025
%F A068985 1/e = Sum_{n >= 0} binomial(x, n+1)/n! / Sum_{n >= 0} (-1)^(n+1)*binomial(-x, n+1)/n!, for arbitrary nonzero x. - _Peter Bala_, Nov 07 2025
